                    </div>
                    <span>This is a marvelous book that balances old-fashioned, practical advice with a healthy dose of motivational prose. You can keep a gracious home, just like "Mrs. Dunwoody".</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Timeless Encouragement</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>2</span>
                      /
                      <span>2</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2003-09-19</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Though Mrs. Dunwoody hails from the past, her advice--with the exception of the whitewash recipe--is timeless. This book is a great encouragement to those who long for well-kept home. The book is funny with enough amusing details from our foremothers (see whitewash recipe) to keep them human while reminding us of what was so great about grandmother's house. Helpful, amusing, and tender as a mother's touch. You've got to get it!</span>
                  
              
